11/07/2008
ANKARA, Turkey -- Police on Thursday (July 10th) arrested the suspected driver of the car used in Wednesday's attack against the US consulate in Istanbul that claimed six lives, local media reported. 
The suspect allegedly managed to escape after police killed three of his associates.
In other news, ten militants from the terrorist Kurdistan Workers' Party and one village guard were killed on Friday in clashes in the southeast province of Sirnak, CNN Turk reported. 
No further information is immediately available. 
(Sabah, Turkish Press, Euronews, CNN Turk, Hurryet - 11/07/08; Reuters - 10/07/08)
